## 4. Data Flow

### Main Use Case: Needle-in-a-Haystack (`main.py`)

```
main()
  │
  ├── generate_massive_context(1_000_000 lines)  → context: str (giant multiline string)
  │
  └── rlm.completion(context=context, query="What is the magic number?")
        │
        ├── setup_context()
        │     ├── build_system_prompt() → messages = [{"role":"system", "content": REPL_SYSTEM_PROMPT}]
        │     ├── convert_context_for_repl(context) → (None, context_str)
        │     └── REPLEnv(context_str=context_str)
        │           └── load_context() → writes context.txt to /tmp/repl_env_XXXX/
        │                               → exec("with open(context.txt) as f: context = f.read()")
        │
        └── for iteration in range(max_iterations=10):
              │
              ├── llm.completion(messages + next_action_prompt(query, iteration))
              │     → root LLM response (may contain ```repl ... ``` blocks)
              │
              ├── find_code_blocks(response)  [utils.py:4]
              │     → ["chunk = context[:100000]\nanswer = llm_query(...)"]
              │
              ├── repl_env.code_execution(code)  [repl.py:265]
              │     ├── exec(code, {**globals, **locals})
              │     │     └── llm_query("...chunk...") → Sub_RLM.completion(prompt)
              │     │           → LLMClient.completion() → Gemini API → sub-answer
              │     └── returns REPLResult(stdout, stderr, locals, exec_time)
              │
              ├── add_execution_result_to_messages(messages, code, result)
              │     → appends {"role":"user", "content": "REPL output: ..."} to messages
              │
              └── check_for_final_answer(response, repl_env)  [utils.py:114]
                    → finds FINAL_VAR(answer) in response
                    → reads repl_env.locals["answer"]
                    → returns the magic number string
```

